	<question>
		<p>
			<line>The two blocks attempt to find the smallest of three numbers.</line>
		</p>
		<img>
			<name height="4">47.1.png</name>
			<name height="4">47.2.png</name>
		</img>
		<p>
			<line>Given the buggy _CODES_smallest of three_CODEE_, which values of A, B and C reveal the bug?</line>
		</p>
	</question>
	<answers>
		<option id="c1">
			<p>
				<line>
					A=1, B=2, C=3
				</line>
			</p>
		</option>
		<option id="c2" correct="true">
			<p>
				<line>
					A=1, B=3, C=2
				</line>
			</p>
		</option>
		<option id="c3">
			<p>
				<line>
					A=2, B=1, C=3
				</line>
			</p>
		</option>
		<option id="c4">
			<p>
				<line>
					A=2, B=3, C=1
				</line>
			</p>
		</option>
		<option id="c5">
			<p>
				<line>
					A=3, B=1, C=2
				</line>
			</p>
		</option>
		<option id="c6">
			<p>
				<line>
					A=3, B=2, C=1
				</line>
			</p>
		</option>
	</answers>
	<hint>bug occurs when a smaller than b and c, but c is smaller than b</hint>
